cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a drone-based object tracking and 3D localization scheme using deep learning-based object detection. This involves computer vision algorithms and robotics, which are covered by the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. The use of deep learning also suggests the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method, which suggests the Learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the paper involves the localization of objects in 3D space, which is related to the Graphics (cs.GR) category.
